---
const layers = [
  { id: '01', name: 'Problem Capture', desc: 'Why was this built? What alternatives were considered? What constraints existed?' },
  { id: '02', name: 'Decision Tracking', desc: 'What tradeoffs were made? What was the reasoning? How did the spec evolve?' },
  { id: '03', name: 'Execution Mapping', desc: 'How did decisions translate to code? What patterns were followed? What was tested?' },
  { id: '04', name: 'Outcome Analysis', desc: 'Did implementation match the spec? Where did execution diverge from the plan?' },
];
---

<section class="py-[120px] px-10 border-t border-border bg-bg-secondary" id="intelligence">
  <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto">
    <div class="max-w-[600px] mb-20">
      <div class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-text-dim mb-5">The Advantage</div>
      <h2 class="font-display heading-style text-[clamp(32px,4vw,48px)] leading-tight">
        The first decision-to-code dataset.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-20">
      <div>
        <p class="text-[21px] text-text-primary leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Today's AI models learn from code. But code alone doesn't capture why something was built, what alternatives were considered, or what tradeoffs were made.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Every project in Ultraviolet links the original problem, the decisions made, and the final code. This creates a dataset no one else has&mdash;how software is actually built, end to end.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          That means better planning, better execution, and intelligence that compounds with every feature your team ships.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-0.5">
        {layers.map((layer) => (
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[48px_1fr] gap-5 py-5 px-6 bg-bg-primary border-l-2 border-border transition-colors hover:border-text-dim">
            <div class="font-mono text-xs text-text-dim">{layer.id}</div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-display heading-style text-lg mb-1">{layer.name}</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-text-secondary">{layer.desc}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
